  "original_lang": "ta",
  "original_title": "\u0b85\u0bae\u0bc6\u0bb0\u0bbf\u0b95\u0bcd\u0b95 \u0b89\u0baf\u0bb0\u0bcd\u0bae\u0b9f\u0bcd\u0b9f\u0b95\u0bcd\u0b95\u0bc1\u0bb4\u0bc1 \u0b87\u0ba9\u0bcd\u0bb1\u0bc1 \u0b87\u0bb2\u0b99\u0bcd\u0b95\u0bc8 \u0bb5\u0bb0\u0bc1\u0b95\u0bbf\u0bb1\u0ba4\u0bc1",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "US High Level delegation arrives in Sri Lanka today",
      "author": "T. Saranya",
      "body_lines": [
        "A high-level delegation representing the US State Department and the Treasury Department will arrive in Sri Lanka today (26) to discuss with various parties how Sri Lanka can assist in recovering from the current economic crisis.",
        "The delegation, which includes the US Treasury Deputy Secretary of State for Asia, Robert Cabroth, and US Secretary of State for South and Central Asia Kelly Gaitling, will stay in Sri Lanka until next Wednesday (29) to meet with representatives of various political parties, economists and international organizations.",
        "The meetings will focus on ways to help Sri Lanka, which is facing a major economic crisis, the steps being taken by Sri Lankans to address the current economic crisis, and plans for future sustainable and inclusive economy building.",
        "US Ambassador to Sri Lanka Julie Sung said the visit was a reaffirmation of the US commitment to the security and prosperity of the Sri Lankan people. 'Sri Lankans are currently facing the worst economic crisis in their history. Our assistance in the economic development of Sri Lanka and in strengthening the democratic framework is much needed in the current context, \u201dhe said.",
        "The United States has announced $ 120 million over the past two weeks to provide $ 120 million for small and medium-sized businesses in Sri Lanka, as well as $ 27 million for Sri Lankan dairy production and $ 5.75 million to provide much needed assistance to those most severely affected by the economic crisis.",
        "In this context, the US Embassy in Sri Lanka has stated that the United States will continue to provide the necessary assistance to recover from the economic crisis in the future, to deal appropriately with the food security crisis and to improve the public health service, and strongly supports Sri Lanka's decision to seek the International Monetary Fund."
      ],
